Reverse 9-1-1 is a public safety communications technology developed by Airbus DS Communications, a unit of Airbus Group, Inc. It is used by public safety organizations in Canada and the United States to communicate with groups of people in a defined geographic area. The system uses a database of telephone numbers and associated addresses, which, when tied into geographic information systems (GIS), can be used to deliver recorded emergency notifications to a selected set of telephone service subscribers. Reverse911 is trademarked by Airbus DS Communications.
